      "header": "The DALI toolkit",
      "text": "The DALI project offers a multilingual toolkit with playful and game-based resources. The toolkit contains a set of educational games and resources addressed to adult learners and educators. The DALI games aim to encourage data literacy through game-based and flexible learning strategies. On this page, you can find resources to help facilitate playful learning using the DALI games.",
      "image-url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martinheitmann/dali-website-content/main/image-assets/dali_img1.png",
      "align-text": "center",
      "image-width": 150,
      "image-height": 150
    },
    {
      "header": "The materials",
      "text": "The DALI Framework for Data Literacy contains four elements: (1) Understanding Data, (2) Acting on Data, (3) Engaging Through Data and (4) Ethics and privacy. The DALI framework is based on the latest standards and, inspired by the complexities of data literacy, provides a comprehensive roadmap for individuals to navigate the data-driven world effectively.",
      "image-url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martinheitmann/dali-website-content/main/image-assets/dali_img2.png",
      "align-image": "right",
      "align-text": "center",
      "image-width": 150,
      "image-height": 150
    },
    {
      "text": "The DALI Handbook is an educational guide to help you make the most of DALI resources, ensuring they are engaging and valuable. Each game is integrated into a Game-Based Networked Learning Strategy (GBNLS), containing advice on planning, implementing and evaluating the game sessions. The GBNLS will give facilitators and educators a better understanding of the pedagogical proposals that underlie the games—including their social and pedagogical design.",
      "image-url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martinheitmann/dali-website-content/main/image-assets/dali_img3.png",
      "align-image": "left",
      "align-text": "center",
      "image-width": 150,
      "image-height": 150
    },
    {
      "text": "The DALI Facilitator’s Guide supplements the handbook by introducing more in-depth and practical advice on activating learning before playing, during playtime and closing learning sessions when using the toolkit.",
      "image-url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martinheitmann/dali-website-content/main/image-assets/dali_img4.png",
      "align-image": "right",
      "align-text": "center",
      "image-width": 150,
      "image-height": 150
    }
  ],
